{
  "doc_id": "25254",
  "text": "In MANETs, the forwarding node set for broadcast is usually selected in a localized manner, where each node determines its own status of forwarding or non-forwarding based on local information [CITATION_1] , or the status of a node is designated by its neighbors [CITATION_2] . A smaller-sized forwarding node set is considered to be more efficient due to the reduced number of transmissions in the network, which helps to alleviate the interference and also conserves energy. The connected dominating set (CDS) as a virtual backbone has been widely studied [CITATION_3] , where each node is either a forwarding node or a neighbor to a forwarding node in the set, and the set is connected. Finding a minimum CDS is NP-complete.",
